#system(DTIME - day/time manipulation routines)
#module(ADD_DAYS,11/01/78)
Add a given number of days to an internal day/time.
#usage
EXTERNAL FUNCTION ADD_DAYS(DTIME: DTIME_INT;
   NUM_DAYS: DAYS): DTIME_INT;
#input(DTIME)a day/time in internal form.
#input(NUM_DAYS)a (possibly negative) number of days.
#output(<return value>)an internal day/time formed by adding
the specified number of days to the given day/time.
If a negative day/time would result then the internal day/time
for day zero is returned.
